1. Introduction

This Privacy Policy describes how this Discord bot (“the Bot”) collects, uses, and stores data.

By using the Bot, you agree to the practices outlined here.

2. Information We Collect
a. User Data

User ID

Username & Discriminator

Avatar URL (temporary usage)

Permissions used for command execution

b. Server (Guild) Data

Server ID

Channel & Role IDs

Server configuration/settings

Logs (only if enabled explicitly by the server staff)

c. Interaction Data

Slash commands

Button/menu interactions

Event triggers
➡️ These are processed temporarily and not stored unless necessary for a feature.

3. What We Do Not Collect

❌ No message history
❌ No DMs
❌ No personal information
❌ No IP addresses
❌ No emails

We respect user privacy and collect only what is essential for the Bot to operate.

4. How We Use the Data

Data is used for:

Running bot features

Saving server settings

Moderation systems

Logging (if enabled)

Improving performance and stability

Preventing abuse and detecting errors

We never sell or share your data for advertising.

5. Data Storage & Security

Data is stored securely in a database or file system

Only the developer(s) have access

We use reasonable protection measures

Data is kept only as long as needed for features to function

6. Data Sharing

We do not share your data with:

Third parties

Advertisers

External services

Data may be shared only if:

Required by law

Necessary to protect the Bot from abuse

7. User Rights

You have the right to:

Request what data is stored

Ask for data modification

Request deletion of all your stored data

Stop data collection by removing the Bot

8. Data Deletion

You may delete your data by:

Using an in-bot delete/reset command (if available)

Contacting the developer directly

All data will be permanently removed.

9. Third-Party Services

The Bot interacts with:

Discord API

Hosting services (VPS, cloud, etc.)

These services have their own privacy policies.

10. Children’s Privacy

The Bot is not intended for users under 13 years old, in compliance with Discord's Terms.

We do not knowingly collect data from children.

11. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy at any time.
Your continued use means you accept the updated terms.

12. Contact

If you have questions or requests related to your data:
https://discord.gg/HpRdyKPFsB
